Class SimpleKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.AbstractAny

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Any, KeyDef, Serializable

    public class SimpleKey
extends IoKey
implements KeyDef
    A simple key implementation. Instances are not managed and, as such cannot be handled by Transaction implementations like TwoPhaseTransaction.

    • Constructor Detail

      • SimpleKey

        public SimpleKey(String name,
                 Any primary,
                 boolean unique)
        Make a new Simple Key definition. There is no relationship between all keys for a given item and the primary key where SimpleKey is concerned as this class only serves as a bridge to the I/O system and does no caching nor any referential object integrity. This constructor exists only to satisfy the XSL scripts used to create system configurations.
